<subSubSection id="F04DA390D87BD9D4668490BC6FB9C13F" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="C8B4C4F0C55E8289990B392DC7BD6DCB" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="5E083F810890828842B0270CEF859290" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cryptantha glomerulifera" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomerulifera">Cryptantha glomerulifera</taxonomicName>
≡ 
<taxonomicName id="52ED91139E96FB4D58A33202A562BB28" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium glomeruliferum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeruliferum">Eritrichium glomeruliferum</taxonomicName>
Phil., Anales Univ. Chile 90: 521. 1895. Type: Chile. 
<normalizedToken id="F1A26C0E8BBD21A56633DA7EAE3C76F8" originalValue="Región">Region</normalizedToken>
de Coquimbo: Las Mollacas, Cordillera de Illapel, 1888, 
<emphasis id="04232D08A3F8910665C60B1BB506851F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">F. Philippi s.n.</emphasis>
(first-step lectotype, designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="18C7BA21A88FAB8163500B2E42421557" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston 1927</bibRefCitation>
, pg. 56: SGO; second-step lectotype, designated here: SGO [SGO000004088 digital image!]; isolectotypes: GH [GH00096394 digital image!], SGO [SGO000004089 digital image!]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CEF3D19DC7F95353716132C7D389974C" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph id="703CC2E6D2A7E7B2E52634923AE16CCE" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="159752B4716BBCBC912A1D2E5B64FC00" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="1F65414CDA8ED2CD0883920E2E65D8D5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium glomeruliferum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeruliferum">
<emphasis id="1EEAB7AD6BE278A4795B45D6851B546B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium glomeruliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BB5FCAD12534ACFB4626F66D5C987EE7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="511 - 566" refId="B39" refString="Philippi, RA, 1895. Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion). Anales de la Universidad de Chile 90: 511 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" title="Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion)." url="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" volume="90" year="1895">Philippi 1895</bibRefCitation>
) includes a direct reference to a collection made by F. Philippi in Las Mollacas, Chile. Two specimens in agreement with the protologue as referred to by R. A. Philippi are found at SGO. 
<bibRefCitation id="A9A0BE16892E30BBB15D57BB608B674B" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
referred to a specimen kept at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken id="39E2C2A9781C351F831DA0E09772E15F" originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the species name, while 
<bibRefCitation id="1E23DAE620E22AADED1C78AD885B2D54" author="Perez-Moreau, RL" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B30" refString="Perez-Moreau, RL, 1976. Revision del genero Cryptantha en la Argentina (Boraginaceae). Darwiniana 20(1/2): 155-188." title="Revision del genero Cryptantha en la Argentina (Boraginaceae). Darwiniana 20 (1 / 2): 155 - 188." year="1976">
<normalizedToken id="7625F434E589EFDF3E6990D4111CBA11" originalValue="Pérez-Moreau">Perez-Moreau</normalizedToken>
(1976)
</bibRefCitation>
later discussed this name and its original material, stating &quot;Chile. Coquimbo, Las Mollacas, Cordillera de Illapel, s/c, 1-1888 (tipo de 
<taxonomicName id="0054BEC722CCFABB7512B4F9240F9590" genus="E." lsidName="E. glomeruliferum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="glomeruliferum">
<emphasis id="F62C4D5DAB5E350B782D8D0C066A8FA4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">E. glomeruliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, SGO)&quot;. However, the statements made by the authors are insufficiently precise since it cannot be ascertained to which of the specimens at SGO they were referring. Thus, the earliest choice of Johnston is here interpreted as a first-step lectotypification. In order to narrow this designation, the specimen SGO000004088 is here selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
